This directory contains an example dataset to test the CA PacBio RS correction pipeline. The files are:
  - lambda.fasta - the reference for the lambda sequence used for PacBio RS validation
  - asm.spec     - the spec file used for assembly of hybrid datasets (designed for a 16-core machine)
  - pacbio.spec  - the spec file used for correction of PacBio RS sequences (designed for a 16-core machine)
  - pacbio.filtered_subreads.fasta/fastq - the PacBio RS filtered sequence (averaging about 89.6% identity to the reference, with 94.6% average coverage by a match to the reference)
  - illumina.fastq - A simulated Illumina dataset (via wgsim) for the lambda.fasta reference. This is 50X of coverage in unpaired sequences 

To run the correction pipeline:
wgs/Linux-amd64/bin/fastqToCA -libraryname illumina -technology illumina -type sanger -innie -reads illumina.fastq > illumina.frg
wgs/Linux-amd64/bin/pacBioToCA -length 500 -partitions 200 -l pacbio -t 16 -s pacbio.spec -fastq pacbio.filtered_subreads.fastq illumina.frg > run.out 2>&1

To assemble the corrected reads:
wgs/Linux-amd64/bin/runCA -p asm -d asm -s asm.spec pacbio.frg > asm.out 2>&1

The results should be:
head -n 40 asm/9-terminator/asm.qc
[Scaffolds]
TotalScaffolds=1
TotalContigsInScaffolds=1
MeanContigsPerScaffold=1.00
MinContigsPerScaffold=1
